<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="995" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[168,775,644,871]" pageId="10" pageNumber="995">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="995" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,327,644,668]" pageId="10" pageNumber="995">Identification.</emphasis>
Our specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1834" box="[523,656,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="995" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[523,656,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="995">M. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were identified
</emphasis>
based on the short pronotum in the apterous form, not covering the mesonotum (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser N &amp; Melo AL" box="[510,771,712,736]" pageId="10" pageNumber="995" refId="ref16904" refString="Nieser N, Melo AL (1997) Os Heteropteros Aquaticos de Minas Gerais: Guia Introdutorio com Chave de Identificacao para as Especies de Nepomorpha e Gerromorpha. Editora UFMG, Belo Horizonte, 177 pp." type="book" year="1997">Nieser and Melo 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Padilla-Gil DN &amp; Moreira FFF" box="[168,506,746,770]" pageId="10" pageNumber="995" pagination="587 - 595" refId="ref17143" refString="Padilla-Gil DN, Moreira FFF (2013 a) Two new species of Microvelia Westwood, 1834 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae) from Colombia, with a key to Colombian species. Zootaxa 3745 (5): 587 - 595. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3745.5.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Padilla-Gil and Moreira 2013a</bibRefCitation>
), and the bent hind tibia of the males. Males are elongated, with the sides of body more or less parallel, whereas females are much more robust and rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
